      • SiteDataSet

        public SiteDataSet(java.lang.String domain)
            throws SiteDataSet.DuplicateDomainException
        Constructs an instance for a specific domain. The instance of most each represent a unique domain. If an instance already exists for a given domain, an exception will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        domain - the domain for which this SED will store data
        Throws:
        SiteDataSet.DuplicateDomainException - thrown if a SED for the specified domain already exists
